AGI - A devastating fire broke out in the night between Saturday 15 and Sunday 16 March 2025 at the Pulse disco in Kočani, about 100 km east of Skopje, North Macedonia >. According to the Macfax agency, the victim's budget rose to 51 deaths and over 100 wounded >, while in the club there were about 1,500 people > to attend a concert by the hip-hop duo DNK
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h3> cause of fire: fireworks on stage </h3>
According to the local press, the fire would be caused by fireworks placed on the stage > which triggered the flames in the crowded room. Some DNK band members would be among the wounded. The local authorities have initiated an investigation to verify compliance with the local security rules and establish any liability. The Minister of the Interior, Pance Toskovski, said: <em>“</em>The exact causes of the stake will be determined and all the responsible will respond.” Some organizers of the event were arrested, while others are among the injured.
<h3>Tre days of national mourning and suspension of the football championship
The Macedonian authorities have proclaimed three days of national mourning in memory of the victims. Prime Minister Hristijan Mickoski> has ensured that the government is mobilized to address the consequences of the tragedy and identify the responsible. Federcalcio macedone> announced the suspension of the championship as a sign of respect for the victims. Meanwhile, affected families are receiving psychological support and assistance from local institutions.
